# UI Guidelines

## Mobile-first
- Design at 375px width first, then scale up
- Tap targets min 44×44px
- Bottom-sheet patterns preferred over modals on mobile
- Avoid hover-only interactions — must work on touch

## Tailwind
- Use semantic tokens from shadcn theme (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`)
- NEVER hardcode colors like `bg-[#ff0000]` — extend theme if needed
- Spacing: stick to the 4px scale (`p-2`, `p-4`, `p-6`, `p-8`)

## Components
- Compose from shadcn/ui primitives in `components/ui/`
- Loading states: use `<Skeleton />` for data, `<Spinner />` for actions
- Empty states: always have an illustration or icon + helpful text + primary action
- Error states: user-friendly message + retry button; never show raw error strings

## Forms
- Use `react-hook-form` + `zod` for validation
- Validate on blur, submit on explicit action
- Show inline errors below fields, not as toasts
- Disable submit button while submitting; show spinner in button

## Accessibility
- Every interactive element has an accessible name
- Use semantic HTML — `<button>` for actions, `<a>` for navigation
- Focus states must be visible (don't remove outlines)
- Color is never the only indicator (add icons or text)

## Date/time display
- Always use the org timezone from context, never `new Date().toLocaleString()` without TZ
- Use `date-fns` + `date-fns-tz` for formatting and parsing
- Show relative times for recent events ("2 min ago"), absolute for future ("Tomorrow 10:00 AM")
